  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Asian Paints Limited  versus Ram Babu & Another pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_7_573_592','2025INSC828'); ><font size='4'> <strong>ASIAN PAINTS LIMITED <span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>RAM BABU & ANOTHER </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 573</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 828</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002942025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : AHSANUDDIN AMANULLAH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASHANT KUMAR MISHRA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the appellant-company falls under the definition of &lsquo;victim&rsquo; in terms of s.2(wa) r/w the proviso to s.372, CrPC or whether s.378, CrPC would prevail in the facts and circumstances; whether an appeal under CrPC would be restricted only to mean an appeal to the First Appellate Court or include even an appeal to the Second Appellate Court/High Court. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; s.2(wa) r/w proviso to s.372; s.378 &ndash; Counterfeit products were sold in the<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 14-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2952/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_7_573_592','2025INSC828','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-seconda